<div class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-blue-50 to-gray-100 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8 md:p-12 space-y-10">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="text-center space-y-4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900">About TripHeatmap</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Data-driven neighborhood rankings to help travelers find the best places to stay in cities worldwide
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Mission -->
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Our Mission</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          TripHeatmap was created to solve a common travel problem: finding the right neighborhood to stay in an unfamiliar city.
          Instead of relying on subjective reviews or marketing hype, we use real venue data and quantitative metrics to rank
          neighborhoods based on their vibrancy, walkability, and dining/nightlife density.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Our proprietary Vibrancy Index analyzes the density, diversity, and volume of restaurants, bars, and cafés to give
          travelers an objective measure of each neighborhood's energy and appeal. Whether you're looking for a foodie paradise,
          a nightlife hub, or a quiet residential area with great local spots, our data helps you make informed decisions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- What We Offer -->
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">What We Offer</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-blue-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Interactive Heatmaps</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Visualize neighborhood vibrancy across entire cities with our color-coded maps showing restaurant, bar, and café density.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-green-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Data-Driven Rankings</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Every neighborhood is scored on a 0-10 scale using our Vibrancy Index formula based on real venue data.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-purple-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Detailed Guides</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              Get comprehensive neighborhood profiles with amenity counts, area size, sample venues, and practical insights.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-amber-200">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Global Coverage</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
              We cover major cities across North America, Europe, Asia, Oceania, and South America, with new cities added regularly.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- How It Works -->
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">How It Works</h2>
        <ol class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">1</span>
            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">Data Collection:</span> We aggregate venue data from public databases and open data portals to map every restaurant, bar, and café in each neighborhood.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">2</span>
            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">Vibrancy Calculation:</span> Our algorithm analyzes density (venues per km²), diversity (variety of venue types), and volume (total amenity count) to generate a 0-10 score.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">3</span>
            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">Ranking & Tagging:</span> Neighborhoods are ranked by their vibrancy scores and tagged based on their strengths (e.g., "Foodies," "Nightlife," "Remote Workers").
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">4</span>
            <div>
              <span class="font-semibold">Visualization:</span> We present the data through interactive maps and comprehensive guides to help you explore and compare neighborhoods.
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <!-- Who We Are -->
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Who We Are</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          TripHeatmap is run by a team of travel enthusiasts and data scientists who believe that better information leads to
          better travel experiences. We started this project after countless hours spent researching neighborhoods on generic
          booking sites and inconsistent travel blogs. We wanted a simple, data-driven way to answer the question: "Where should I stay?"
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Our platform is built for modern travelers who value authenticity, walkability, and local culture. We don't take payments
          from hotels or neighborhoods for better rankings – our data speaks for itself. Every neighborhood is evaluated on the same
          objective criteria, ensuring fair and unbiased recommendations.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Coverage -->
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8 space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Our Coverage</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We currently cover over 100 cities across 25+ countries, including major destinations in:
        </p>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">North America</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">United States, Canada, Mexico</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Europe</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">UK, France, Germany, Spain, Italy, and more</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Asia</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Japan, Thailand, Singapore, UAE, Vietnam</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Oceania</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Australia, New Zealand</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">South America</h4>
            <p class="text-gray-600">Argentina, Brazil</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Contact CTA -->
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-8">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-blue-700 rounded-lg p-8 text-center text-white space-y-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Have Questions or Feedback?</h3>
          <p class="text-blue-100">
            We'd love to hear from you. Whether you have suggestions for new features, cities to add, or general feedback, get in touch!
          </p>
          <%= link_to "Contact Us", contact_path, class: "inline-block mt-4 px-6 py-3 bg-white text-blue-600 font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-50 transition" %>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Footer Links -->
      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 pt-6 text-center">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-6 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_path, class: "hover:text-blue-600 underline" %>
          <%= link_to "Terms of Service", terms_path, class: "hover:text-blue-600 underline" %>
          <%= link_to "Contact", contact_path, class: "hover:text-blue-600 underline" %>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
          © <%= Time.current.year %> TripHeatmap. All rights reserved.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
